# =========================================================================
# Risk Assessment
# =========================================================================

## Critical Gaps (block release)

1. ModelRegistry.compare() -- P0 engine missing a spec method. Users cannot
   compare two model versions programmatically.

2. ExperimentTracker unwired -- Engine is implemented but inaccessible from
   the public API. One-line fix in __init__.py.

## Significant Gaps (should fix before release)

3. DataExplorer.compare() -- spec method missing. Cannot compare two datasets.

4. interop.from_arrow() and dict_records_to_polars() -- listed in spec but
   absent. Breaks round-trip interop story.

5. Benchmark harness -- no evidence that the <15% overhead criterion has
   been validated. Success criterion from the plan cannot be verified.

6. HyperparameterSearch successive_halving -- advertised as a strategy but
   delegates to random search. Misleading API.

## Minor Gaps (can ship with known limitations)

7. ModelSerializer not centralized -- functionality exists across two modules.
   Not user-facing but diverges from architecture spec.

8. CONVERSION_OVERHEAD_NOTE.md -- documentation gap only.

9. RL onnx_status -- minor metadata inconsistency.

10. FeatureEngineer.register_to_feature_store() -- convenience method, not core.

11. TrainingPipeline Nexus endpoints -- InferenceServer has them, TrainingPipeline does not.
    Users can still trigger training programmatically.
